cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CE 

The paper discusses topics related to adaptation and self-organization in evolving systems, which are central to the field of Evolutionary Computation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper aims to improve the performance of Evolutionary Algorithms (EA), which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the relation between EA and natural evolution, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Learning). Furthermore, the incorporation of new mechanisms for mimicking complex biological systems could be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
